## TypeScript

Applies to {{ 'frontend/ and docs-site/' if (include_frontend and include_docs_site) else ('frontend/' if include_frontend else 'docs-site/') }}.

- **Type everything.** `tsconfig.json` has `strict: true` â€” no new `any`; prefer a real type or
  `unknown` with a narrowing check. `tsc --noEmit` must pass.
- **Formatting:** `prettier --check .`. **Linting:** `eslint` (`eslint-config-next`, incl. the
  `core-web-vitals` subset of `jsx-a11y`).
- **Components:** Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only where interactivity
  requires it. Keep components small and colocate a component with what only it uses.
{%- if include_frontend %}
- **HTTP goes through `lib/api-client.ts`**, never a bare `fetch` at a call site â€” that is how a
  codebase ends up with a dozen error behaviours and no timeouts. It retries **idempotent methods
  only**; if a mutation must be retried, make it idempotent first.
- **Every route that can fail independently gets an `error.tsx`.** One throwing component must
  not blank the page.
- **Security headers live in `next.config.ts`.** Known gap: `script-src` still allows
  `'unsafe-inline'` because Next's bootstrap requires it without a nonce â€” add nonce middleware
  before this app handles sensitive data. COEP is intentionally off (it breaks cross-origin
  assets and is only needed for cross-origin isolation).
- **Watch the bundle budget** (`npm run bundle-size`). Raise `BUNDLE_MAX_KB` deliberately, with a
  reason â€” not reflexively when it goes red.
{%- endif %}
- **Never interpolate a copier value (project name, slug) into a formatter-checked line.** A long
  or quoted value can push the line past the prettier/ruff limit or break the syntax on a fresh
  generation. Put anything that must vary in a small JSON module and import it instead â€” see
  `app/site.json`{% if include_frontend and include_docs_site %} in `frontend/` and `docs-site/`{% elif include_frontend %} in `frontend/`{% else %} in `docs-site/`{% endif %}.
{% endif %}
## Tests

- Every new behaviour has a test; security-relevant code **requires** tests.
- **Backend:** fast, isolated, deterministic (in-memory SQLite for the DB layer).
{%- if include_frontend %}
- **Frontend:** `vitest` + `@testing-library/react`, colocated under `frontend/tests/`. Assert
  structure/behaviour (roles, text presence), not exact copy â€” see `frontend/tests/page.test.tsx`
  for the pattern.
{%- endif %}

## Commits & PRs

- **Conventional Commits.** One logical change per commit.
- PRs run the full gate + doc-consistency guards; the PR template lists the Definition of Done.
